🧹 5. Data Preprocessing Steps

Loaded dataset using pandas.read_csv("expenses.csv").

Inspected data with data.head() to check column names and values.

Converted “Amount” to a NumPy array for calculations.

Grouped data by Category and Date using groupby().

Sorted data by highest spending categories.


📊 6. Data Analysis and Visualizations
🔹 Step 1 – Calculate Total & Average Expense
total_expense = np.sum(amounts)
average_expense = np.mean(amounts)


Output Example:
💰 Total Expense: ₹12,450
📈 Average Expense: ₹1,245.00

🔹 Step 2 – Category-wise Expense Summary

Grouped and sorted categories:

category_summary = data.groupby('Category')['Amount'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)


 Helps identify top spending areas.

🔹 Step 3 – Bar Chart: Category-wise Expense

A bar chart displays total spending per category.
The highest expense category is highlighted in 🟧 orange.

🔹 Step 4 – Line Chart: Daily Expense Trend

A line chart shows how total expenses change by date.
Used to identify spending peaks and dips.

💡 7. Key Insights

📍 Highest spending category is easy to identify from the bar chart.
📍 Total and average expenses show overall financial behavior.
📍 Daily trends reveal which days have more spending.
📍 Even a small dataset can give meaningful insights with proper visualization.

